          "body": "Verses 5-8 contain the longest block of direct first-person divine speech in the book. Through twenty chapters, God has been seen, sung to, and announced — but rarely heard speaking. Here He pronounces six things in His own voice: (1) the universal renewal (v. 5a); (2) the reliability of the prophecy (v. 5b); (3) the consummation (v. 6a, *gegonan*); (4) His own identity as Alpha and Omega (v. 6b); (5) the gracious provision for the thirsty and the inheritance for the overcomer (vv. 6c-7); (6) the exclusion of the unrepentant (v. 8). The oracle is structured like a covenant ceremony — promise, identity, gift, condition, sanction. The same eight-vice list (v. 8) reappears in 22:15 as the chapter's bookend exclusion."
